\frametitle{Outer Products}

  \begin{itemize}
  \item The function \texttt{outer()} is sometimes useful in
    statistical calculations. It can be used to perform an operation
    on all possible pairs of elements coming from two vectors.

  \item Example

\begin{verbatim}
> x1 <- seq(1, 5)
> outer(x1, x1, "/")
> y <- seq(5, 10)
> outer(x1, y, "+")
\end{verbatim}

  \end{itemize}
